definition.value: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia pulex.
A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3E)-dec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.
A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3Z)-9-methyldec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.

A spiroketal and delta-lactone resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-glutamine with the anomeric hydroxy group of D-fructose and substitution of the 1-hydroxy group of the fructose by the alpha-amino group of the glutamine. It is found in crown gall tumours induced in chrysanthemums by Agrobacterium tumefaciens.
A chrysopine formally derived from alpha-D-fructopyranose.
A chrysopine formally derived from beta-D-fructopyranose.
A  sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (4Z,7Z)-deca-4,7-dien-1-ol with sulfuric acid.
A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3Z)-dodec-3-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-yl group.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-yl group.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a decyl group.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a nonyl group.
A lipoate that is the conjugate base of (R)-lipoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by an octyl group.
A polymyxin having a (6R)-6-methyloctanoyl group at the amino terminus.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (9-methyldecyl) group.
A lipoyl-AMP(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of (R)-lipoyl-AMP; major species at pH 7.3.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (1R,4S)- and (1S,4R)-benzovindiflupyr. A fungicide that is active agaist a range of cereal diseases.
A dihydrolipoate that is the conjugate base of (R)-dihydrolipoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A lipoamide obtained by condensation of the carboxy group of (R)-lipoic acid with ammonia.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (8-methylnonyl) group.
The (R)-enantiomer of S(6)-acetyldihydrolipoamide.

An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-amine.
A member of the class of sulfamic acids that is sulfamic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens has been replaced by a (7-methyloctyl) group.
An N(6)-lipoyl-L-lysine residue in which the lipoyl group has R-configuration.
An N(6)-dihydrolipoyl-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.
An iron(III) hydroxamate isolated from fungi and bacteria including Penicillium species and Neurospora crassa. It is a growth factor for coprophilous fungi.
An N-[9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl]-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (1R,4S)-enantiomer of benzovindiflupyr.
An N(6)-(S(8)-aminomethyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.
An alkyl alcohol that is 2,6-dimethylheptane carrying a hydroxy group at position 1.
An N-[9-(dichloromethylene)-1,2,3,4-tetrahydro-1,4-methanonaphthalen-5-yl]-3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (1S,4R)-enantiomer of benzovindiflupyr.

An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 3',4'-dichloro-5-fluorobiphenyl-2-amine. A fungicide for use in cereals for key stem and leaf disease control including strobilurin-resistant septoria.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.
An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of  2,6-dimethylheptan-1-ol.
The (S)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.
The (R)-enantiomer of 2,6-dimethylheptyl hydrogen sulfate.
An N(6)-(S(8)-acetyldihydrolipoyl)-L-lysine residue in which the dihydrolipoyl group has R-configuration.
An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of (4R)-4,8-dimethylnonan-1-ol.

An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3-(difluoromethyl)-1-methylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 3',4',5'-trifluorobiphenyl-2-amine. Used to control a number of cereal fungal pathogens including those belonging to the Ascomycetes, Basidiomycetes and Zygomycetes families.
A sulfuric ester obtained by the formal condensation of (3S,4E)-3-methyldec-4-en-1-ol with sulfuric acid.
A sulfuric ester of (3Z)-dec-3-en-1-ol.
A sulfuric ester of (3Z,6Z)-dodeca-3,6-dien-1-ol.
A sulfuric ester of (3Z,6Z,9Z)-dodeca-3,6,9-trien-1-ol.
An aromatic amide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 5-chloro-1,3-dimethylpyrazole-4-carboxylic acid with the amino group of 1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-amine.
A 5-chloro-1,3-dimethyl-N-(1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-yl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of furametpyr.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of N(6)-[(R)-S(8)-succinyldihydrolipoyl]-L-lysine residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of decanol.
An alkyl sulfate that is the sulfuric ester of  octan-1-ol.
A 5-chloro-1,3-dimethyl-N-(1,1,3-trimethyl-1,3-dihydro-2-benzofuran-4-yl)pyrazole-4-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of furametpyr.
